⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Teddy Dang
node GDS · GDS · ⟦Teddy Dang:GDS:d03046⟧

WHO   — Teddy Dang — the target of the film's worst bit
WHAT  — Named honestly, not as a joke: the figure a Pearl-Harbor war-speech incites a mob to beat — a bit condemned on release.
WHERE — GDS · The Goods (2009)  Framework inputs: The Goods: Live Hard, Sell Hard (2009, dir. Neal Brennan, Gary Sanchez/Paramount Vantage); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because honesty about this film means naming, and not laundering, the cruelty aimed at him.
HOW   — By being conflated with a wartime enemy and beaten as a punchline — the gag the JACL and MANAA condemned.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  The film turned me into a punchline for a racist beating, and real people called it out by name. I am where the comedy failed.

